rComments: The best prof I ever have. Clear grading criteria, you know where you got wrong. He also gives you a partial mark which is amazing. Homework was acceptable, not very difficult. If this is your mandatory course, you should take it with him. All the best!!!!!!!

Overall a good prof. Participation matters. Hard projects and assignments. Midterm is not that hard. He does give feedbacks during a lecture. Did not reply to any of the emails I have sent. I would recommend this prof. if you are not here for the mark.

If this class isn't mandatory don't take it, it will be a waste of your time and money with this prof. He is very disorganized and a poor lecturer. The final project is a mess and ended up being completely changed for most students less than a week before the due date. Avoid this prof to save your sanity.

Good prof, flexible and willing to help students, make sure you attend class because he values participation. Read the textbook chapters. Project is hard but doable and graded fairly easily, assignments take time, exams are fair but definitely need to study well for them. Past exams are very helpful.

He's actually very caring towards students and spent much time answering all of our questions about our assignments and upcoming exams. I really appreciated that because some profs don't prepare you at all. Tough course though with confusing project. Make sure to read the textbook and spend time on assignments! It's the best way to pass.
Don't take this course, you will regret it.

I don't know how to describe this prof aside from I was so unprepared by this man that I stopped being mad and just stopped expecting anything from him. He does not give back marks online. It has been over a month since class ended and I still don't know my marks for about 60% of the course. Horrible, Avoid at all costs.

Lectures are useless. In order to do well in this class you'll have to slog through a textbook as well as watch videos and lectures on youtube from other universities. The project was also completely useless and contributes very little to the learning objectives of the course. It's not a surprise that the course is being removed as a requirement.

He's worse than useless. To pass: + read the slides +read the corresponding sections in the textbook +memorize the algorithms (Step 1: Do this. Step 2: Do that. ...) +do a good job on the assignments +don't waste too much time on the project (it's not going to work) Don't worry, you won't see complex questions (like in assignments) on the tests.

Highly unorganized. (Even instructions for assignments are confusing) Has a hard accent and tough to understand (So, lects not super useful ) Makes easy concepts sound so tough. (You lose passion for the subject ) NEVER RESPONDS TO EMAILS! (You heard it right.) P.S. You are on your own. Be self-motivated and you can surely survive the course!

Worst prof I've ever had. Hard to understand, teaches the subject poorly, unorganized, doesn't answer emails, extremely confusing assignments and project that you're expected to figure out on your own, etc. Luckily, he makes the exams easy to make up for his shortcomings as a teacher, absolutely the worst prof at uOttawa.

Worst prof ever. Avoid at all cost. I was not able to understand a word of what he says in class. He never response to his emails. Did not pick a midterm date until a week before. He says he is going to send emails about something then never does. He does not show up to his own office hours. Just DON'T TAKE HIS CLASS.
He is very flexible and helps students to address problems but he is not easily available over email

Worst class of my life.  Skims through the slides in class, skips parts you need to know.  Not sure what's important what's not.    Whatever is written on the board will most likely be on the exam.   Disorganized and arrogant.
I don't usually blame teachers, but he is unclear and makes the simplest of topics very roundabout. Read the textbook and save your time.  The project is the definition of suffering.

The slides and the textbook are bad, and the professor is a HORRIBLE lecturer and slightly delusional. He thinks he's a great teacher and is befuddled when students don't understand (continuously). Then, to cover it all up, he makes his exams easy so people pass. I needed 2 textbooks to even grasp the material (I'm an A student usually). Good luck.
Very unorganized class. Don't take it unless you have to.  Worst prof I have ever seen in the university.

Assignments were easy, midterm was tougher (no cheat sheet), was allowed one printed sheet of notes on the final which saved everyone. For the project just look it up on Github since the lab slides suck.

Really hard to understand. His slides are very disorganized. I've never heard a teacher say, "this is complicated, so I won't teach it to you. Go learn it on your own" before. Almost NEVER responds to emails. Tried to take his class and dropped it twice because I couldn't deal with him. Said textbook was optional, but assignments were all from it.

The worst professor I ever had. He doesn't know how to speak english properly. He doesn't care if you understand him or not. His lectures are poor. His slides are worst, so prepare yourself to search your answers in somewhere else. You can try to read the +1k pages book, good luck if you have time! He is also arrogant.
God bless you if you have to take his class.
Very unorganized
He's the worst. I want to die while in his class
He's really mean
really hard to understand
he give the hardest project ever
Horrible. Very strong accent. Makes things more complicated than they should be.
BAD
Terrible
He's not good, you will regret taking this teacher

Very disorganized with assignments, and especially the project. His solution for the first stage of the project had several large mistakes and differed from the original schema he provided. We were required to use his solution for the rest of the project, which caused a great deal of confusion and frustration. Has strong accent, hard to understand

Before he should teach, he should take a course in pronounctation. He has a terrible smell that kills even mosquitos. If you want to take his class. Just tell him that you are a CEO of a company and you will get A+. Garanteed !!
He covers the subject matter in an effective, if condescending, fashion.  Try to participate in class  if you want him to take you seriously during office hours.

Extremely Arrogant... treats you like a piece of**** if you don't have A+ or if you are not looking forward to do a master or P.h.d. Always turn very simple things into very complicated ones... For him, simple explanation are for college students...
No Comments

I completely agree. Very arrogant and temperamental. He's just released the first assignment. After a while, he sends us an email saying that only a few has come to ask for help so he 'withholds' his hints on the assignment. What kinda prof does that?
I completely agree with the previous evaluation. Furthermore, 50% of our French group goes to the Enligh class.
Very arrogant and tempermental. Extremely disorganized when dealing with assignments - moves around dates and requirements.
